#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/using-superpowers/references/gemini-tools.md
M|references|Skills use Claude Code tool names. When you encounter these in a skill, use your platform equivalent:
M|references|| Skill references | Gemini CLI equivalent |
M|references||-----------------|----------------------|
M|references|| `Read` (file reading) | `read_file` |
M|references|| `Write` (file creation) | `write_file` |
M|references|| `Edit` (file editing) | `replace` |
M|references|| `Bash` (run commands) | `run_shell_command` |
M|references|| `Grep` (search file cnt) | `grep_search` |
M|references|| `Glob` (search files by name) | `glob` |
M|references|| `TodoWrite` (task tracking) | `write_todos` |
M|references|| `Skill` tool (invoke a skill) | `activate_skill` |
M|references|| `WebSearch` | `google_web_search` |
M|references|| `WebFetch` | `web_fetch` |
M|references|| `Task` tool (dispatch subagent) | No equivalent — Gemini CLI does not support subagents |
M|references|Gemini CLI has no equivalent to Claude Code's `Task` tool. Skills that rely on subagent dispatch (`subagent-driven-dev`, `dispatching-parallel-agents`) will fall back to single-ses execution via `exec
M|references|These tools are available in Gemini CLI but have no Claude Code equivalent:
M|references|| Tool | Purpose |
M|references||------|---------|
M|references|| `list_directory` | List files and subdirectories |
M|references|| `save_memory` | Persist facts to GEMINI.md across sessions |
M|references|| `ask_user` | Request structured input from the user |
M|references|| `tracker_create_task` | Rich task management (create, update, list, visualize) |
M|references|| `enter_plan_mode` / `exit_plan_mode` | Switch to read-only research mode before making changes |